cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper is about Natural Language Generation (NLG), which is a subfield of Computational Linguistics (CL) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely categories. NLG also involves machine learning and deep learning techniques, which are covered in cs.LG. Additionally, NLG has applications in information retrieval (IR) and software development (SD), which are covered in cs.IR and cs.SD respectively.
